The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 30 January is 189,929 (21,890.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 25 January, there were 9,888 new confirmed cases (1,139.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 18 January, there were 8,123 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 22% (1,765 extra cases).
